@{
  Layout = "_Layout";
}

  <div class="container">
    <div class="jumbotron">
      <h1 class="shadow">Tamagotchi Simulator</h1>
      <p>Add some tamagotchis and try to keep them alive by using the Feed, Play, and Rest buttons.</p>
      <a href="#" id="rulesBtn" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#rulesModal">View Rules</a>
      <form>
        <div class="input-group">
          <input type="text" name="name" id="name" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter pet name...">
          <span class="input-group-btn">
            <button id="add-pet" class="btn btn-default" type="submit">Add Tamagotchi</button>
          </span>
        </div>
      </form>
    </div>
    <div class="life-cycle-box">
        <h3 class="light-shadow center">Life Cycle Timer</h3>
        <div class="progress">
            <div class="progress-bar progress-bar-info" id="life-cycle-bar" role="progressbar" aria-valuenow="45" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100" style="width: 0%">
                <span class="sr-only">45% Complete</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-container">
      @{
          await Html.RenderPartialAsync("_DisplayPetData");
      }
    </div>
    <div class="modal fade" id="rulesModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel">
      <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
        <div class="modal-content">
          <div class="modal-header">
            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
            <h1 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">Rules</h1>
          </div>
          <div class="modal-body">
            <p>- Add a tamagotchi to start the life cycle timer.</p>
            <p>- Every 10 seconds, the <span class="bold-text">life cycle timer</span> will remove a random value from your pet's stats.</p>
            <p>- Click the <span class="bold-text">Feed</span>, <span class="bold-text">Play</span>, or <span class="bold-text">Rest</span> buttons to refill different portions of your pet's stat pools.</p>
            <p>- Gain <span class="bold-text">exp</span> and <span class="bold-text">level up</span> by keeping stat pools above 0 during each life cycle tick.</p>
            <p>- Leveling up will add a random amount to your stat pools.</p>
            <p>- If any stat falls below 0, or a life cycle tick drops a stat below 0, your pet will die.</p>
            <p>- If your pet dies, <span class="bold-text">bury</span> it and try again! See if you can beat your previous record!</p>
            <p>- For an extra challenge, try adding multiple pets!</p>
            <h3>Additional Notes:</h3>
            <p><span class="bold-text">Feed: </span>Adds a medium replenish to the <span class="bold-text">Hunger</span> pool, adds a minor replenish to the <span class="bold-text">Happiness</span> and <span class="bold-text">Energy</span> pools.</p>
            <p><span class="bold-text">Play: </span>Adds a major replenish to the <span class="bold-text">Happiness</span> pool, adds a minor decay to the <span class="bold-text">Hunger</span> and <span class="bold-text">Energy</span> pools.</p>
            <p><span class="bold-text">Rest: </span>Adds a medium replenish to the <span class="bold-text">Happiness</span> and <span class="bold-text">Energy</span> pools, adds a minor decay to the <span class="bold-text">Hunger</span> pool.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="modal-footer">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
